                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.840 Welles, Sumner/127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 15, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 60, March 14, 6 p.m. Department is requesting Paris to repeat to you
                    text of memorandum handed to Reynaud by Mr. Welles. It is understood that Mr.
                    Welles delivered same memorandum to other Governments he visited. The Department
                    is contemplating a more comprehensive communication to the states in
                        consultation.<note n="24" xml:id="d22fn24">See telegram No. 33, April 4, 7
                        p.m., to the Minister in Switzerland, and footnote 91, <ref target="#pg_122"
                            >p. 122</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
